UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393284900254
AB  - It is well known that perfect foresight maximizing models frequently possess a continuum of equilibria. In some of these equilibria the price level is explosive even in models in which the money supply is constant. This paper shows that a sufficient condition to rule out these unstable paths is given by the assumption that there is a smallest non-zero unit of output.
